<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/css/style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/css/public.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="public-container">
        <div class="public-header">
            <h1>About Location Tracking</h1>
            <p>Educational demonstration of location tracking technology</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="content-section">
            <div class="info-card">
                <h2>üéì Educational Purpose</h2>
                <p>This application is designed for educational purposes to demonstrate how location tracking works in web applications. It shows the capabilities and limitations of browser-based location tracking.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info-card">
                <h2>üîç What This Tool Does</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Location Tracking:</strong> Records GPS coordinates from your device</li>
                    <li><strong>Real-time Updates:</strong> Continuously monitors location changes</li>
                    <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Collects basic device and browser information</li>
                    <li><strong>Accuracy Measurement:</strong> Shows how accurate the location data is</li>
                    <li><strong>Consent Management:</strong> Requires explicit user consent before tracking</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info-card">
                <h2>üõ°Ô∏è Privacy & Security</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Consent Required:</strong> We always ask for permission before tracking</li>
                    <li><strong>Temporary Storage:</strong> Data is stored temporarily and automatically deleted</li>
                    <li><strong>No Unauthorized Sharing:</strong> Your data is not shared with third parties</li>
                    <li><strong>Educational Use Only:</strong> Data is used solely for demonstration purposes</li>
                    <li><strong>User Control:</strong> You can stop tracking at any time</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info-card">
                <h2>üîß Technical Details</h2>
                <h3>Data Collected:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>GPS coordinates (latitude, longitude)</li>
                    <li>Location accuracy (in meters)</li>
                    <li>Timestamp of each location update</li>
                    <li>Browser information (user agent, platform)</li>
                    <li>Screen resolution and language settings</li>
                    <li>IP address for security purposes</li>
                    <li>Battery level (if available)</li>
                    <li>Connection type (WiFi, cellular, etc.)</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>How It Works:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>User clicks on a tracking link</li>
                    <li>Browser requests location permission</li>
                    <li>User grants or denies permission</li>
                    <li>If granted, location is tracked at regular intervals</li>
                    <li>Data is sent to the server and stored temporarily</li>
                    <li>Administrator can view tracked locations in real-time</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info-card">
                <h2>‚öñÔ∏è Legal & Ethical Considerations</h2>
                <div class="warning-box">
                    <h3>‚ö†Ô∏è Important Notice</h3>
                    <p>Location tracking without consent is illegal in many jurisdictions and violates privacy rights. This tool is designed for:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Educational purposes only</li>
                        <li>Demonstrating web technologies</li>
                        <li>Understanding privacy implications</li>
                        <li>Testing with willing participants</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Never use this tool to track anyone without their explicit consent.</strong></p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info-card">
                <h2>üéØ Use Cases</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Educational Demonstrations:</strong> Teaching about location APIs</li>
                    <li><strong>Privacy Awareness:</strong> Showing how location tracking works</li>
                    <li><strong>Security Testing:</strong> Testing location security measures</li>
                    <li><strong>Development Learning:</strong> Understanding geolocation implementation</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info-card">
                <h2>üîí Your Rights</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>You have the right to know what data is collected</li>
                    <li>You can withdraw consent at any time</li>
                    <li>You can request deletion of your data</li>
                    <li>You can ask questions about data usage</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="privacy-links">
            <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
            <a href="/">Home</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
